main event: An unidentified object was observed over Deer Park, Maryland, on March 10, 1965, hovering and then departing in a southerly direction.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 5 minutes,The object was seen in daylight,The observer described it as a small round white light,The object appeared to move smoothly and steadily across the sky,The conclusion of the investigation was 'FAIL CR' indicating no credible report.
witness description: Civilian observer who reported seeing an unidentified object
